channel.title: CVE Feed for Zyxel -- GS1900 series firmware
channel.description: The latest CVEs for Zyxel -- GS1900 series firmware

item.title: CVE-2021-35031|2024-08-04T00:33:49.873Z -- zyxel -- gs1900%20series%20firmware
item.description: A vulnerability in the TFTP client of Zyxel GS1900 series firmware, XGS1210 series firmware, and XGS1250 series firmware, which could allow an authenticated LAN user to execute arbitrary OS commands via the GUI of the vulnerable device.

item.title: CVE-2021-35032|2024-08-04T00:33:49.889Z -- zyxel -- gs1900%20series%20firmware
item.description: A vulnerability in the 'libsal.so' of the Zyxel GS1900 series firmware version 2.60 could allow an authenticated local user to execute arbitrary OS commands via a crafted function call.
